Lower all the way down and come to a prone position. Engage your pelvic floor to support your spine and pull the lower belly in, getting ready to rise up against gravity. Press the front bones of your pelvis into the ground to open your hip joints and nutate the sacrum. On your inhale, lift your chest off the grounds, sending your sternum up and forward to create length. Make sure to keep your legs straight and fully engage your quads. Press the iliac crest the ground while extending energy out through your big toe. Feel the lengthening sensation through your whole body

